This paper deals with the computational complexity of the Clique problem in interval graphs, which is a classic problem in computational graph theory. The paper also introduces the concept of 3-track interval graphs, which is a specific type of interval graph. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
